	   <a name=10498006926940></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f10498006926940><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=16324&mid=10498006926940>Awesome</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=16324&mid=10498006926940#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=207834><span id= >Sknorb</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>1 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Apr 8th 7:55 AM 2003</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I bought one for 19k and I have not one regret. I was using Soulstripper for a while which has the 75pt lifetap but the melee damage on it just didn't cut it for soloing.<br><br>With all melee stats maxxed at (or above) 255, this weapon doesn't stop proccing. I tested it out on goranga followers in ME and it procced 21 times during the first fight. I repeated and it went off like crazy. Max melee hit is 140ish so far and add the 75pt proc damage and this is a very nice weapon.<br><br>There is a downfall to this weapon though. If you are fighting mobs that are immune to stun spells yu can hold agro an entire fight. I was in the factory in PoI where the clockwork golems were immune to the stun. I slowed/maloed/crippled, waited for the mob to be down to 60% before going in and I still stole agro and kept it every time the stun proc got resisted. The golems still took the 75pt proc but the stun resist can get you killed in there, especially if you are with the monk and rogue attacking from the back and you pull agro during an enrage.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
