	   <tr><td colspan=2>Nope, thats not true. NOBODY who does not have dual wield can equip a weapon in their offhand.<br><br>What you are probably confusing, is that there are some carried ITEMS, that have weapon graphics. I know necros have a scythe graphic item, but it has NO MELEE STATS (damage/delay)<br><br>There is also a parrying dagger, which LOOKS like a dagger, but only has AC, no damage/delay.<br><br>Any item with damage/delay statistics, can only be equipped in secondary AFTER dual wield skill is activated, and only on classes that CAN dual wield. I found this out with my warrior, at a very low level, when I was given a weapon that had a shield graphic (Shield of the slain unicorn). I was not able to equip it, until I got dual wield.<br><br>So this hammer can not be put in secondary for the stats. <br><br>The reason it says either melee, is that that is the default for all 1h weapons, and the developers didn't bother to flag it as primary only, since none of the classes listed have dual wield anyway.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Jan&nbsp;&nbsp;8 12:15:38 2003</em><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
